Loan Data Exploration¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others attributes.

# convert CreditGrade, ProsperRating, and IncomeRange into ordered categorical types
ordinal_var_dict = {'CreditGrade': ['AA','A','B','C','D','E','HR','NC'],
                    'ProsperRating (Alpha)': ['AA','A','B','C','D','E','HR'],
                    'IncomeRange': ['$0', 'Not employed', '$1-24,999', '$25,000-49,999', '$50,000-74,999', '$75,000-99,999', '$100,000+']}

for var in ordinal_var_dict:
    pd_ver = pd.__version__.split(".")
    if (int(pd_ver[0]) > 0) or (int(pd_ver[1]) >= 21): # v0.21 or later
        ordered_var = pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(ordered = True,
                                                    categories = ordinal_var_dict[var])
        Loans[var] = Loans[var].astype(ordered_var)
    else: # pre-v0.21
        Loans[var] = Loans[var].astype('category', ordered = True,
                                             categories = ordinal_var_dict[var])
In [11]:
# To define a function to add one new purpose of the loan descripton column . Which will help to make Easy readable visualization. 
def Loan_purpose(x):
    """ quick function for getting the Loan purpose description based on number"""
    list_values = ['Not Available','Debt Consolidation','Home Improvement','Business','Personal Loan','Student Use','Auto','Other','Baby&Adoption','Boat',
             'Cosmetic Procedure', 'Engagement Ring','Green Loans','Household Expenses','Large Purchases','Medical/Dental','Motorcycle', 
             'RV','Taxes','Vacation','Wedding Loans']; 
        
    return list_values[x];
    
Loans['category'] = Loans['ListingCategory (numeric)'].apply(Loan_purpose)

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

There are 1,13,937 Loans in the dataset with 81 features (LoanOriginalAmount,BorrowerAPR,BorrowerRate,ProsperRating (numeric),TotalProsperLoans,StatedMonthlyIncome,ClosedDate,Etc). Most variables are folating & objects in nature, but the variables CreditGrade, ProsperRating, and IncomeRange are ordered factor variables with the following levels.

CreditGrade: ['AA','A','B','C','D','E','HR','NC'], ProsperRating : ['AA','A','B','C','D','E','HR'], IncomeRange : ['$0', 'Not employed', '$1-24,999', '$25,000-49,999', '$50,000-74,999', '$75,000-99,999', '$100,000+']

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I'm most interested in figuring out what features are best for defining the interest rate of Loans in the dataset.¶

What are the factors to define the loan Amount ?¶

Which states was buying More loans ?¶

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I expect that Loan Amount,Term,Listing Category,Credit Rating & Proper Rating will have the strongest prediction on each Loan s records:I also think that the other IncomeRange,StatedMonthlyIncome,occupation will have define the interest rate.

In [37]:
# compute the logarithm of price to make multivariate plotting easier
def log_trans(x, inverse = False):
    """ quick function for computing log and power operations """
    if not inverse:
        return np.log10(x)
    else:
        return np.power(10, x)

Loans['Log_LoanAmount'] = Loans['LoanOriginalAmount'].apply(log_trans)
